msgctxt "mn93:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 93 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 93 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn93:0.2"
msgid "Assalāyanasutta "
msgstr "With Assalāyana "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli2.147, sc1
msgctxt "mn93:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn93:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn93:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena nānāverajjakānaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ pañcamattāni brāhmaṇasatāni sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasanti kenacideva karaṇīyena. "
msgstr "Now at that time around five hundred brahmins from abroad were residing in Sāvatthī on some business. "

msgctxt "mn93:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then those brahmins thought, "

msgctxt "mn93:2.3"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti. "
msgstr "“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes. "

msgctxt "mn93:2.4"
msgid "Ko nu kho pahoti samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti? "
msgstr "Who is capable of having a dialogue with him about this?” "

# NOTE: vuttasira only occurs here and in identical passages. The contrast with the normal brahmanical abuse of the muṇḍaka is noteworthy. Also note that in the counterpart passage for old brahmins, a series of words for the age is found here. We thus should find that vuttasira doesn’t just mean shaven, but refers to a specific time of life. According to Manu 2.65, the ceremony of kesanta signifying Vedic studentship is to be given to brahmins at 16, so this must be meant here.
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn93:3.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena assalāyano nāma māṇavo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati daharo, vuttasiro, soḷasavassuddesiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū sanighaṇḍukeṭubhānaṃ sākkharappabhedānaṃ itihāsapañcamānaṃ, padako, veyyākaraṇo, lokāyatamahāpurisalakkhaṇesu anavayo. "
msgstr "Now at that time the brahmin student Assalāyana was residing in Sāvatthī. He was young, newly tonsured; he was sixteen years old. He had mastered the three Vedas, together with their vocabularies, ritual, phonology and etymology, and the testament as fifth. He knew philology and grammar, and was well versed in cosmology and the marks of a great man. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn93:3.2"
msgid "Atha kho tesaṃ brāhmaṇānaṃ etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then those brahmins thought, "

msgctxt "mn93:3.3"
msgid "“ayaṃ kho assalāyano māṇavo sāvatthiyaṃ paṭivasati daharo, vuttasiro, soḷasavassuddesiko jātiyā, tiṇṇaṃ vedānaṃ pāragū … pe … anavayo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:3.4"
msgid "So kho pahoti samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti. "
msgstr "“This Assalāyana is capable of having a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc2
msgctxt "mn93:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho te brāhmaṇā yena assalāyano māṇavo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "So they approached Assalāyana and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn93:4.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bho assalāyana, samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti. "
msgstr "“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes. "

#. VAR: paṭimantetū”ti → patimantetunti (bj, pts1) | paṭimantetunti (mr)
msgctxt "mn93:4.3"
msgid "Etu bhavaṃ assalāyano samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetū”ti. "
msgstr "Please, Mister Assalāyana, have a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "mn93:4.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, assalāyano māṇavo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca: "
msgstr "When they said this, Assalāyana said to them, "

msgctxt "mn93:4.5"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dhammavādī; "
msgstr "“They say that the ascetic Gotama is a speaker of principle. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.6"
msgid "dhammavādino ca pana duppaṭimantiyā bhavanti. "
msgstr "But speakers of principle are hard to have a dialogue with. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.7"
msgid "Nāhaṃ sakkomi samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti. "
msgstr "I’m not capable of having a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.148, sc4
msgctxt "mn93:4.8"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho te brāhmaṇā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "For a second time, those brahmins said to him "

msgctxt "mn93:4.9"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bho assalāyana, samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti. "
msgstr "“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes. "

#. VAR: paṭimantetu → patimantetuṃ (bj, pts1) | paṭimantetuṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn93:4.10"
msgid "Etu bhavaṃ assalāyano samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetu. "
msgstr "Please, Mister Assalāyana, have a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.11"
msgid "Caritaṃ kho pana bhotā assalāyanena paribbājakan”ti. "
msgstr "For you have lived as a wanderer.” "

msgctxt "mn93:4.12"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho assalāyano māṇavo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca: "
msgstr "And for a second time, Assalāyana refused. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.13"
msgid "“samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dhammavādī; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:4.14"
msgid "dhammavādino ca pana duppaṭimantiyā bhavanti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:4.15"
msgid "Nāhaṃ sakkomi samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetun”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "mn93:4.16"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho te brāhmaṇā assalāyanaṃ māṇavaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "For a third time, those brahmins said to him, "

msgctxt "mn93:4.17"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bho assalāyana, samaṇo gotamo cātuvaṇṇiṃ suddhiṃ paññapeti. "
msgstr "“This ascetic Gotama advocates purification for all four classes. "

#. VAR: paṭimantetu → patimantetuṃ (bj, pts1) | paṭimantetuṃ (mr)
msgctxt "mn93:4.18"
msgid "Etu bhavaṃ assalāyano samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetu. "
msgstr "Please, Mister Assalāyana, have a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.19"
msgid "Caritaṃ kho pana bhotā assalāyanena paribbājakaṃ. "
msgstr "For you have lived as a wanderer. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.20"
msgid "Mā bhavaṃ assalāyano ayuddhaparājitaṃ parājayī”ti. "
msgstr "Don’t admit defeat before going into battle!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "mn93:4.21"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, assalāyano māṇavo te brāhmaṇe etadavoca: "
msgstr "When they said this, Assalāyana said to them, "

msgctxt "mn93:4.22"
msgid "“addhā kho ahaṃ bhavanto na labhāmi. "
msgstr "“Clearly, gentlemen, I’m not getting through to you when I say: "

msgctxt "mn93:4.23"
msgid "Samaṇo khalu, bho, gotamo dhammavādī; "
msgstr "‘They say that the ascetic Gotama is a speaker of principle. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.24"
msgid "dhammavādino ca pana duppaṭimantiyā bhavanti. "
msgstr "But speakers of principle are hard to have a dialogue with. "

msgctxt "mn93:4.25"
msgid "Nāhaṃ sakkomi samaṇena gotamena saddhiṃ asmiṃ vacane paṭimantetunti. "
msgstr "I’m not capable of having a dialogue with the ascetic Gotama about this.’ "

msgctxt "mn93:4.26"
msgid "Api cāhaṃ bhavantānaṃ vacanena gamissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Nevertheless, I shall go at your bidding.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli2.149, sc7
msgctxt "mn93:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho assalāyano māṇavo mahatā brāhmaṇagaṇena saddhiṃ yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "Then Assalāyana together with a large group of brahmins went to the Buddha and exchanged greetings with him. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho assalāyano māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one side and said to the Buddha: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn93:5.3"
msgid "“brāhmaṇā, bho gotama, evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "“Master Gotama, the brahmins say: "

msgctxt "mn93:5.4"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo; "
msgstr "‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.5"
msgid "brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo; "
msgstr "Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.6"
msgid "brāhmaṇova sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā; "
msgstr "Only brahmins are purified, not others. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.7"
msgid "brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’ti. "
msgstr "Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’ "

msgctxt "mn93:5.8"
msgid "Idha bhavaṃ gotamo kimāhā”ti? "
msgstr "What do you say about this?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Dissanti → dissante (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn93:5.9"
msgid "“Dissanti kho pana, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ brāhmaṇiyo utuniyopi gabbhiniyopi vijāyamānāpi pāyamānāpi. "
msgstr "“But Assalāyana, brahmin women are seen menstruating, being pregnant, giving birth, and breastfeeding. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.10"
msgid "Te ca brāhmaṇiyonijāva samānā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Yet even though they’re born from a brahmin womb they say: "

msgctxt "mn93:5.11"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo; "
msgstr "‘Only brahmins are the highest caste; other castes are inferior. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.12"
msgid "brāhmaṇova sukko vaṇṇo, kaṇho añño vaṇṇo; "
msgstr "Only brahmins are the light caste; other castes are dark. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.13"
msgid "brāhmaṇāva sujjhanti, no abrāhmaṇā; "
msgstr "Only brahmins are purified, not others. "

msgctxt "mn93:5.14"
msgid "brāhmaṇāva brahmuno puttā orasā mukhato jātā brahmajā brahmanimmitā brahmadāyādā’”ti. "
msgstr "Only brahmins are Brahmā’s rightful sons, born of his mouth, born of Brahmā, created by Brahmā, heirs of Brahmā.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6
msgctxt "mn93:6.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti: "
msgstr "“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.” "

msgctxt "mn93:6.2"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:6.3"
msgid "brahmadāyādā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "mn93:6.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Assalāyana? "

msgctxt "mn93:6.5"
msgid "sutaṃ te: ‘yonakambojesu aññesu ca paccantimesu janapadesu dveva vaṇṇā—ayyo ceva dāso ca; ayyo hutvā dāso hoti, dāso hutvā ayyo hotī’”ti? "
msgstr "Have you heard that in Greece and Persia and other foreign lands there are only two classes, masters and bonded servants; and that masters may become servants, and servants masters?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn93:6.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho, sutaṃ taṃ me: ‘yonakambojesu aññesu ca paccantimesu janapadesu dveva vaṇṇā—ayyo ceva dāso ca; ayyo hutvā dāso hoti, dāso hutvā ayyo hotī’”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, I have heard that.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn93:6.7"
msgid "“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?” "

msgctxt "mn93:6.8"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:6.9"
msgid "brahmadāyādā’”ti? "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn93:7.1"
msgid "“Kiñcāpi bhavaṃ gotamo evamāha, atha khvettha brāhmaṇā evametaṃ maññanti: "
msgstr "“Even though you say this, still the brahmins maintain their belief.” "

msgctxt "mn93:7.2"
msgid "‘brāhmaṇova seṭṭho vaṇṇo, hīno añño vaṇṇo … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:7.3"
msgid "brahmadāyādā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.150, sc9
msgctxt "mn93:7.4"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, assalāyana, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Assalāyana? "

msgctxt "mn93:7.5"
msgid "khattiyova nu kho pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya, no brāhmaṇo? "
msgstr "Suppose an aristocrat were to kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct; to use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and to be covetous, malicious, with wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. Would this happen only to an aristocrat, and not to a brahmin? "

msgctxt "mn93:7.6"
msgid "Vessova nu kho … pe … "
msgstr "Or suppose a merchant, "

msgctxt "mn93:7.7"
msgid "suddova nu kho pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya, no brāhmaṇo”ti? "
msgstr "or a worker were to act in the same way. Would that result befall only a merchant or a worker, and not to a brahmin?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn93:7.8"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bho gotama. "
msgstr "“No, Master Gotama. "

msgctxt "mn93:7.9"
msgid "Khattiyopi hi, bho gotama, pāṇātipātī adinnādāyī kāmesumicchācārī musāvādī pisuṇavāco pharusavāco samphappalāpī abhijjhālu byāpannacitto micchādiṭṭhi kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyya. "
msgstr "If they acted the same way, the same result would befall an aristocrat, a brahmin, a merchant, or a worker. "

msgctxt "mn93:7.10"
msgid "Brāhmaṇopi hi, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:7.11"
msgid "vessopi hi, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:7.12"
msgid "suddopi hi, bho gotama … pe … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn93:7.13"
msgid "sabbepi hi, bho gotama, cattāro vaṇṇā pāṇātipātino adinnādāyino kāmesumicchācārino musāvādino pisuṇavācā pharusavācā samphappalāpino abhijjhālū byāpannacittā micchādiṭṭhī kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapajjeyyun”ti. "
msgstr "For if any of the four classes were to kill living creatures, steal, and commit sexual misconduct; to use speech that’s false, divisive, harsh, or nonsensical; and to be covetous, malicious, with wrong view, then, when their body breaks up, after death, they’d be reborn in a place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn93:7.14"
msgid "“Ettha, assalāyana, brāhmaṇānaṃ kiṃ balaṃ, ko assāso yadettha brāhmaṇā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "“Then what is the source of the brahmins’ self-confidence and forcefulness in this matter that they make this claim?” "

